ONMEL should be taken with a full meal at the same time each day. The recommended dose is 200 mg (one tablet) once daily for 12 consecutive weeks.
Limited data are available on the use of oral  itraconazole in patients with renal impairment. Caution should be exercised when ONMEL is administered to patients with renal impairment. [See CLINICAL PHARMACOLOGY and WARNINGS AND PRECAUTIONS]
Limited data are available on the use of oral itraconazole in patients with hepatic impairment. Caution should be exercised when ONMEL is administered to patients with hepatic impairment. [See CLINICAL PHARMACOLOGY and WARNINGS AND PRECAUTIONS]
